title: For Sale:  AR-15 5.56 Caliber Professionally Built
postcontent:
This is a sale of a set of custom built AR-15's in 5.56 caliber and LR-308's in 7.62 x 51 (.308) caliber, all of which are running some of the best parts available. They were custom built by a Gunsmith that was in the process of completing his Master Gunsmith License with a specialty in the field of Semi-Auto and Full Auto type weapons. He was required to build 10 Guns to be submitted for grading purposes. I was lucky enough to be able to procure a number of these guns which I will be listing for sale here and other sites, with a new one being featured as each one is sold.  There is a very limited number available, and the prices are very reasonable for custom built guns, and once they are gone, there will be no more. All of these Guns were graded at an A+ grade based on functionality, performance, durability, and fit & finish.  All of these guns have been test fired by the senior instructor for grading purposes (none of the guns have had more than 20 rounds through them). These guns will fire any type of ammo from the cheapest to the best quality, and they do not stall out no matter how fast you pull the trigger. I was amazed at the speed in which these guns fire being semi-auto's. As they were hand built. The triggers vary in pull weight (most around the 5 lb range), and all of them have very clean crisp let off with little to no creep. You must use caution when firing these weapons, because the triggers are so highly polished and set, they fire as soon as you touch the triggers, something most of us are not accustomed to. When I say no creep I really mean no creep.  

This listing is for a basic configuration camouflage AR-15 in 5.56 caliber (which allows you to also shoot the cheaper .223 rounds if you choose to).  Here is the list of parts utilized in building this gun by section. The upper is put together with a DPMS 7075-T6 Billet Upper, FN SS 1:7 Twist Barrel, Midwest Industries SSG12G2 Full Length Free Float Upper, Standard A2 Style Muzzle Brake, Ares 5.56 NiB Bolt, and BCM Stock Charging Handle. The Lower is put together with a Viper Open Trigger Guard 7075-T6 billet lower, and CMMG LPK, the pistol grip is a standard GI Pistol Grip. The Stock is assembled from a 6 position Blackhawk Parts Kit with a Heavy Duty Rubber Recoil Pad, the Fore Grip is a CAA FVG Folding 5 position lockable grip with storage, and the sights are flip-up machined aluminum style sights.  The additional pieces include the following: 1 QD Sling attachments with a Medium Duty Sling, 2 forward rails for these extras to be mounted on, 1 CAA Polymer 30 round magazine, and the gun is finished in Camouflage DuroCoat with a Matte Gloss UV Clear Coat Finish. This Gun comes fully assembled and packed nicely in a single gun case. 


You can purchase this prized AR-15 for the very reasonable price of $1639.54. The comparables of this gun are all well into the $1800.00 - $2000.00 range.  I am passing on my good fortune to you, but this price is firm, and I will not take trades.  This is a cash only private party sale (no checks, money orders or credit cards accepted).  This sale does not require and FFL. I may be willing to warranty parts for 90 days from date of purchase if you specify this as part of the sale, but will require the broken part (un-cleaned, as-is) to ensure no abuse which would void warranty (using low grade ammo or using .223 ammo also voids parts warranty) you will have to provide proof of caliber, type, lot# and manufacturer of ammo (plus one unused round) to invoke parts warranty.  I will perform powder analysis to ensure ammo stated is true.  All sales are final.
